gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 130, Knicks 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks defeated the Knicks, 130-111. Giannis Antetokounmpo led the Bucks with 28 points, seven rebounds, and seven assists as Bobby Portis (23 points, 11 rebounds) and Khris Middleton (20 points, five rebounds, five assists) totaled 43 points as Milwaukee shot 16-32 from beyond the arc. Jalen Brunson led the Knicks with 36 points and seven assists. The Bucks have now won seven in a row and improve to 22-7. The Knicks move to 16-12.
